<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101975937155940></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101975937155940><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6803&mid=101975937155940>RE: You off i think</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6803&mid=101975937155940#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=44165><span id= >The Glorious OakwoodMoonblaze</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>88 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 25th 2:36 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>you are right.&nbsp;&nbsp;the formulas are<br>wis below 200: mana = wis/5 * level<br>wis over 200: mana = wis/10 * level<br><br>to go the other way (mana to wis) we have<br>wis below 200: wis = mana * 5 / level<br>wis above 200: wis = mana * 10 / level<br><br>from this we can easily see that at low levels + mana items are better than + wis, and that at high wisdom, mana is better than wis.<br><br>so if your wis is less than 200, with this item you are gaining an effective (35*5 / level) wis.  at level 10, that is equal to ~17 wis, and at 60 it is equal to ~3 wis.<br><br>so if your wis is less than 200, with this item you are gaining an effective (35 * 10 / level) wis.  at level 10, that is equal to ~35 wis, and at 60 it is equal to ~6 wis.<br><br>so is it good?  depends on your level, how much wis you will loose to equip it, total current wis, and total wis with this item on.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
